 The Oracle Cloud Infrastructure (OCI) team can provide you the opportunity to build and operate a suite of massive scale, integrated cloud services in a broadly distributed, multi-tenant cloud environment. OCI is committed to providing the best in cloud products that meet the needs of our customers who are tackling some of the worldâ€™s biggest challenges.
 OCI Data Science  is an exciting new team in OCI hyper-focused on delivering innovative services addressing challenges at the intersection of data science, machine learning, artificial intelligence, big data, and cutting-edge cloud infrastructure. We are building cloud services for a comprehensive AI/ML and data science platform that are targeted to power several OCI services, and AI/ML use cases in enterprise applications and multi-tenant SaaS/ISV applications. Our product vision includes interactive notebooks, distributed machine learning on CPU/GPU supporting wide variety of ML algorithms/libraries, scalable model serving and robust monitoring and analytics for ML models. Our product vision also includes the ability for enterprises to customize these services for their specific business need and to automate MLOps at scale while incorporating these AI/ML solutions in mission critical applications.
 We are specifically looking for a Technical Program Manager to join the OCI Data Science team. You will work closely with product and engineering counterparts and be responsible for managing complex, cross-organizational programs that impact delivery and operations of the OCI Data Science service.
 The role of the TPM differs materially from that of a project manager and a program manager. A TPM is able to drive issues beyond what a traditional program manager can do due to deeper technical skills and expertise. A TPM possesses skills of that of a program manager, project manager with technical expertise that is relevant to the service.
 We offer unique opportunities for technical program managers with the expertise and passion to work with engineering teams to solve difficult problems and manage programs while building and operating a distributed, highly-available services and virtualized infrastructure. At every level, we have opportunities for significant technical and business impact, designing and building innovative new systems to power our customerâ€™s business critical applications. These are exciting times in our space - we are growing fast, still at an early stage, and working on ambitious new initiatives. 
 What Youâ€™ll Do
 Define and manage programs and processes for software development, operations, and customer support.
 Take ownership and drive continuous improvement of ongoing service team programs such as the on-call program, service operations bar, release management, etc.
 Apply project management best practices to ad hoc projects ranging from new feature development to compliance audits
 Drive the scrum and other operational practices across the team to support production cloud services, such as creating and maintaining comprehensive project execution related metrics, dashboards and other documentation.
 Facilitate effective teamwork, communication, collaboration and commitment across Engineering, Product Management, Operations, Support, and other key stakeholders to define and deliver complex programs despite competing priorities by having the ability to influence roadmaps and priorities.
 
Specifically:
 Engage with the Oracle cloud infrastructure platform and shared services teams to ensure seamless integration.
 Engage with the platform and corporate architecture and security teams and assist the team in ensuring compliance as well as raise the bar with necessary standards and architecture patterns in terms of the cloud service overall architecture including high availability, disaster recovery, multi-tenancy management, replication etc.
 Identify intra-team issues and drives them to resolution autonomously; identify and work with key stakeholders to drive issues to resolution.
 Build strong relationships across teams to become a force multiplier.
 Represent the product/team up to the Senior Director level independently and at a higher level with appropriate coaching.
 Be the most knowledgeable person in the team about the execution, the trade-offs and the whys behind them.
 Ability to explain your team's analyses and recommendations to leadership while discussing the technical trade-offs in product development with engineers and product managers.
 Demonstrate flexibility and resilience in response to changing or ambiguous situations, directing changes through appropriate review and approval mechanisms.
 Qualifications
 Bachelorâ€™s degree in Computer Science, Engineering or Business Administration; Masterâ€™s degree or equivalent work experience preferred
 5+ years of experience in developing and operating enterprise programs, ideally having experience driving large infrastructure projects.
 Display a demonstrated ability to think broadly and strategically.
 Possess a technology background that enables you to understand the complexities of Oracle Cloud Infrastructure.
 Possess maturity, judgment, negotiation/influence skills, analytical skills, and leadership skills.
 Have the proven ability to work well with product and engineering teams to establish and maintain our roadmap, set appropriate expectations and ensure our product and services meet our high operational excellence standards.
 Hands-on experience with Machine Learning/AI is preferred, but not required.
 Have the ability to represent the team and product to all levels within the company and to ancillary support groups.
 Experience
 Have the expertise to manage complex programs spanning across multiple functions\teams.
 Strong knowledge of and implementation experience with various project management methodologies (Agile, Scrum, Waterfall).
 Have experience with continuous improvement methods or Kaizen processes.
 Possess strong verbal, written communication skills and be detailed oriented.
 Must be willing to work in a fast-paced environment and be willing to adjust to changing priorities while maintaining a can-do attitude.
 Be a self-starter and can work independently. 
 
 
Manage the development and implementation process of a specific company product.
 
 
Manage the development and implementation process of a specific company product involving departmental or cross-functional teams focused on the delivery of new or existing products. Plan and direct schedules and monitor budget/spending. Monitor the project from initiation through delivery. Organize the interdepartmental activities ensuring completion of the project/product on schedule and within budget constraints. Assign and monitor work of systems analysis and program staff, providing technical support and direction.
 
 
Duties and tasks are varied and complex, needing independent judgment. Fully competent in own area of expertise. May have project lead role and or supervise lower level personnel. BS degree or equivalent experience relevant to functional area. 5 years of project management, product design or related experience preferred.
 
 
